kodkod.cli

Class KodkodProblem

  • java.lang.Object
    • kodkod.cli.KodkodProblem

  • public abstract class KodkodProblem
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides a set of actions invoked by the Kodkod parser to specify and solve relational satisfiability problems. A KodkodProblem instance represents either a complete or an incremental specification of a Kodkod problem.

    A complete specification consists of Options, Bounds, a set of asserted formulas, and a problem definition environment. It represents a stand-alone problem description in which each asserted formulas refers to the relations bound the problem's own Bounds instance. Complete specifications are solved with a standard solver.

    An incremental specification also consists of Options, Bounds, a set of asserted formulas, and a problem definition environment. But unlike a complete specification, an incremental specification is composed of a sequence of partial specifications. The first specification in this sequence is a stand-alone problem description. But each subsequent specification may assert formulas that refer to relations that are not bound in its own Bounds instance, as long as they appear in previously specified Bounds.

    Incrementally specified problems are solved with an incremental solver, and the sequence of partial specification describing such a problem must satisfy the requirements imposed by the incremental solving API. For example, the Options, universe and integer bounds can only be configured/declared in the initial specification; they may not be extended or modified in any way by subsequent partial specifications. The IncrementalSolver documentation describes the remaining restrictions in detail.

    All specification action methods return true on success and throw an action exception on failure. References to a problem specification p should be discarded by client code after a reference to a new specification has been obtained from p by calling extend() or clear().

    • Method Detail

      • complete

        public static KodkodProblem complete()
        Returns an empty KodkodProblem that can be used to construct a complete, stand-alone specification of a new relational satisfiability problem. The specification will be initialized with KodkodFactory.baseOptions(). with the given options.
        Returns:
        some p: KodkodProblem | no p.prev && !p.incremental() && p.options = KodkodFactory.baseOptions() && no p.bounds && no p.asserts && p.env = new DefEnv() && p.maxSolutions = 1

      • incremental

        public static KodkodProblem incremental()
        Returns an empty KodkodProblem that can be used to construct the first (stand-alone) component of an incremental specification of a new relational satisfiability problem. The specification will be initialized with KodkodFactory.baseOptions().
        Returns:
        some p: KodkodProblem | no p.prev && p.incremental() && p.options = KodkodFactory.baseOptions() && no p.bounds && no p.asserts && p.env = new DefEnv() && p.maxSolutions = 1

      • extend

        public abstract KodkodProblem extend()
        Returns an empty partial KodkodProblem instance that can be used to extend the incremental specification composed of the sequence of problems ending with this KodkodProblem. Throws ActionException if this is not an incremental specification.
        Returns:
        some p: KodkodProblem | p.prev = this && p.incremental() && p.options = this.options && p.bounds = new Bounds(this.bounds.universe) && no p.asserts && no p.env.parent && p.env.defs = this.env.defs && p.maxSolutions = this.maxSolutions

      • clear

        public abstract KodkodProblem clear()
        Returns an empty KodkodProblem that can be used to construct a stand-alone specification of a new relational satisfiability problem. The returned instance is like this problem in the following sense: it is incremental iff this is incremental; it is initialized with this.options; and it has this.maxSolutions as its limit on the maximum number of solutions.
        Returns:
        some p: KodkodProblem | no p.prev && (p.incremental() iff prototype.incremental()) && p.options = prototype.options && p.maxSolutions = prototype.maxSolutions && no p.bounds && no p.asserts && p.env = new DefEnv()

      • solve

        public abstract KodkodProblem solve(KodkodOutput out)
        Solves this and outputs the resulting solution(s) to the given out. The number of produced solutions is bound above by this.maxSolutions. After solving the problem, this method returns a new empty KodkodProblem that can be used either to extend the specification comprising this problem with additional constraints, if this is an incremental KodkodProblem, or to construct a new complete specification otherwise.
        Returns:
        !this.isIncremental() => this.clear() else this.extend()
        Throws:
        ActionException - any solving pre-conditions are violated

      • env

        public final DefEnv env()
        Returns the problem definitions environment. The relation ('r') register in the returned environment should not be modified by client code, other than through the #declareRelation(String, TupleSet, TupleSet) method. The variable ('v') register of the problem environment is unmodifiable.
        Returns:
        this.env
